%erg v1
Title: Sequence parallel agents rather than fan out when ticket risks budget ceiling
Created: 2026-04-30
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-30T07:30Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

Corpus discovery tickets in chemin-de-voix (0019–0022) each require researching
3–4 figures in parallel. Each beat attempt ends in catastrophic failure: runs 70,
76, 79, 85 (2026-04-30) all show turns=1, cost=$7–9, stop_reason=None. The
pattern is: pick-ticket selects a corpus discovery ticket, raid spawns 3–4
parallel Agent tool calls in turn 1, their combined cost blows through the
per-project budget, beat.py kills the session.

Nothing is committed. The ticket stays open. The next beat picks the same ticket
and repeats the failure. The wasted cost is real: ~$8 × 4 runs = $32 overnight
for chemin-de-voix alone.

The fix the user specified: sequence the sub-agents rather than fan them out.
Commit partial results after each agent completes. If the beat hits budget mid-way,
the completed figures are already committed and the ticket can be continued on
the next beat without re-doing prior work.

## Actions

1. **Detect fanout pattern at raid entry.** Before launching agents, count how
   many parallel Agent calls the ticket body implies. If the estimate exceeds
   the remaining per-project budget by more than 1.5×, switch to sequential mode.

2. **Sequential mode in raid:** work one sub-agent at a time. After each
   sub-agent returns, commit its result immediately (even if the full ticket
   isn't done). Update the ticket log with a `note` entry showing what's been
   completed so far.

3. **Add `parallel-fanout` ticket tag.** Tickets that require ≥3 parallel
   research agents should carry a `parallel-fanout: N` header or body annotation.
   Pick-ticket can use this to estimate cost and decide whether to sequence.

4. **Update beat budget accounting.** When beat.py detects a ticket mid-way
   through sequential execution (partial commit exists), treat remaining cost
   estimate as (total − already spent by prior beats on this ticket).

## Test

- Dry-run a raid on a chemin-de-voix corpus discovery ticket with a $2 budget
  ceiling. Verify: only one sub-agent launches per turn, result is committed
  after each, session terminates cleanly at budget.
- Verify the ticket's log section records partial progress.

## Exit criteria

- No chemin-de-voix corpus discovery beat ends with turns=1 and stop_reason=None.
- Each beat makes at least one committed figure before stopping.
- Full ticket completion spans multiple beats; no work is duplicated.
